geo:siteIdentification.geo:markerDescription: BRASS PLATE; FORCED CENTER STAINLESS STEEL
geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: This station is part of the Western Canada Deformation Array (WCDA)as well as the Canadian Active Control System (CACS) ******************************************** The GPS reference mark consists of a brass plate with a forced centered stainless steel bolt. The brass plate is embedded on top of a 3.0 metre high concrete pier, 60 cm in diameter. The concrete pier is anchored to exposed bedrock using steel re-enforcement bars to a depth of 0.6 m. The antenna is attached to the brass forced centered plate via a 10 cm high anodized aluminum base. This base provides a constant height above the brass plate and also permits the antenna to be referenced to north. ** File Audited as of 2008-06-24
